Package logic

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Character
    The Character class, superclass to every dynamic element in the game
    Drunken
    A type of Guard that can randomly fall asleep and invert the pre-determined path's direction when he wakes up
    DungeonLevel
    The first game level
    DungeonMap
    Map used in the first game level
    EditKeepMap
    Custom map created by user, used in the second game level
    Game
    Game class, the one that holds all the pieces about the current session
    Guard
    Guard, the first level's enemy
    Hero
    The game's main and playable character
    KeepLevel
    The second game level
    KeepMap
    The default map for the second game level
    Level
    Holds all the information necessary about a generic level
    Map
    Holds information about a game map
    Ogre
    Ogre, the second game level's enemy
    Rookie
    A type of Guard that always follows the movement pattern with no exceptions
    Suspicious
    A type of Guard that randomly changes his movement's direction because he can't even trust his shadow
    TestDungeonLevel
    Imitation of the first game level.
    TestDungeonMap
    Map used for Unit testing purposes simulating a smaller version of the first level map
    TestKeepLevel
    Imitation of the second game level.
    TestKeepMap
    Map used for Unit testing purposes simulating a smaller version of the second level map
